claim.claim-text:
Method of controlling a brake motor (12) for a vehicle, comprising generating a brake motor drive signal (Do) in response to an external brake control signal (IB), the method comprising;

providing a primary control branch (510), a backup control branch (520), the primary control branch (510) having a primary inverter (512) and a primary control module (511) to control operation of the primary inverter, the primary control module (511) including at least a first and a second mutually cooperating primary control component (511A, 511B);

the backup control branch (520) having a backup inverter (522) and a backup control module (521) to control operation of the backup inverter;

selecting an operational mode from a plurality of potential operational modes (M0,...,M4) in accordance with a determination of an integrity status (SINT) of both control branches (510, 520), the potential operational modes comprising at least one of a normal operational mode (M1) and a degraded operational mode (M2, M3);

during the normal operational mode (M1) enabling the primary control branch (510) to exclusively generate the brake motor drive signal (Do) in response to the external brake control signal, in which normal operational mode determining an integrity status comprise:
the at least a first and a second mutually cooperating primary control component diagnosing each others integrity status, and
the primary control branch further diagnosing an integrity status of the backup control branch (520) by verifying a response signal (SR) of the backup control branch in response to a test signal (ST).
during the degraded operational mode (M2) enabling the backup control branch (510) to exclusively generate the brake motor drive signal (Do) in response to the external brake control signal.
